    <h2>Homework</h2>
    <p class="text-xl mb-4">PRACTICE DAILY FOR THE REST OF YOUR DOG'S LIFE</p>

    <p class="mb-4">Seriously. Recall is not a "train it once and you're done" skill. You need to practice it regularly, forever. Use it on every walk. Practice in the backyard. Make it part of your daily routine.</p>

    <p class="mb-4">Never stop rewarding it. Even when your dog is 10 years old and has perfect recall, still give them praise and treats every single time they come when called.</p>

    <p class="mb-4">Don't rush off-leash freedom. Many dogs need 6-12 months of long-line work before they're ready for off-leash. And even then, start in enclosed areas like fenced parks.</p>

    <p>A reliable recall opens up a world of freedom for your dog. Hikes without leashes, beach days, camping trips - all of this becomes possible when you trust your dog to come back to you.</p>
